Spending the weekend in Brisbane. My final destination in Australia before flying to New Zealand on Monday. 
I wasn't sure what to expect, but I'm really loving the city. Too bad I can't stay a little bit longer. So if you guys have any tips for things I must (!) do (or eat üòâ) tomorrow, let me know!

Yesterday I went to Whitehaven Beach, but unfortunately didn't have enough time to walk to the Hill Inlet lookout. 
But this is so much better! Flying over the Great Barrier Reef is definitely one of the highlights of this trip. I loved every second of it.
-
Next time I need an assistant though üòÑ. Seeing so much beauty and then taking photos, filming and doing Instagram stories when you only have a couple of seconds...And trying to enjoy the moment at the same time.
It's hard work üòÖ
-
I created a 1 minute video of my flight over the Great Barrier Reef. It's on my Facebook page if you'd like to see it.

#greatbarrierreef

It's been raining for two days here in Airlie Beach. So no beach time, but instead I got to fly over the Great Barrier Reef today which was such an amazing experience!
And like magic, the rain disappeared when we flew over the most beautiful parts of the reef, like this one: Heart Reef üíôüíô
(Check my stories for more from up in the air)

Loved this part of the Great Ocean Road: Loch Ard Gorge. Maybe even more than the 12 Apostles (but don't tell anyone üôä).
-
Today I'm going from the Great Ocean Road to the Great Barrier Reef for more blue water and white beaches. So excited!
How to spot a koala on the Great Ocean Road? Find a group of people standing under a tree looking extremely happy and taking a million photos...There's the koala üê®
